    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nnvim does not resize a windowed terminal based on \"columns=#\" or \"lines=#\" in a modeline.\r\n\r\nIt does however _think_ it has done so.  The status line reflects the modeline's terminal extent.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nCreate a test file containing a modeline that sets columns and lines.\r\n\r\n```\r\n% cat test.txt\r\n# vim: columns=80 lines=25\r\n```\r\n\r\nOpen a terminal window in a reasonably capable windowing terminal program.  I use iTerm2.\r\n\r\nManually resize the terminal window to noticeably wider than 80 columns and visibly taller than 25 lines.\r\n\r\nEdit the test file:\r\n```\r\nenv -i TERM=xterm-256color \"$(which nvim)\" --clean test.txt\r\n```\r\n\r\nnvim will not resize the terminal, but it will place and size the status line as if the terminal did resize.  For example:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"473\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2024-02-22 at 21 32 01\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/81828/6778ed9a-2c1f-4bcf-a34d-46134063258d\">\r\n\r\nExecute `:set lines=26` or `:set columns=81`.  The window should immediately resize to the new extents.  The new settings must be different from the current ones or nvim will assume no resize needs to occur.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expect the `columns=` and `lines=` in a modeline to resize the terminal the way they do when executed manually.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.5. No commit ID reported. `brew info` says: Built from source on 2024-02-11 at 03:06:55\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo, vim resizes the terminal. vim 9.0.1544\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 11.7.10\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\niTerm2 Build 3.4.20\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\n`brew install nvim`, 11 days ago",
